<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tilbake</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-27 13:46:41</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well, just got one of these beuties after weeks of /auc. When I was level 30 I had an opportunity to pick one of these up for 2.2k; sadly I paid 3.5k for this one at level 38 but I had the money and I wanted to drop the lame Spiked Collar. I dont get obbsesed with the game like some and sit with a calculator figuring out haste and stuff like that; however, I do see a HUGE difference in having a higher AC. Me and my friend; both Barbarian Rogues with like stats, chose our paths at around level 30. I decided to go with ful Ravenscale and its AC while he chose to go with STR enhanceing items such as Silver Plated Legs, Dwarven Workboots, and Crested Helm. Now he only had about 10 more STR than me, but my AC was nearly 70 points higher...and we were the same level. I noticed a difference when we soloed (ex. camping the Troll Hide Belt to sell over and over) and he was killed or nearly killed, and I left the same battle with 2-3 bubbles of life. He constantly said I was just getting lucky, but I realized I was taking less damage when I got hit and put two and two together. This item is so great in that it is one of the highest AC neck items, and it has nice stat and save buffs. I think I got ripped for paying 3.5k for it but hell...im banking...who cares, im happy.<BR>
